Class RemoveLocatorsEmpty

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Test, TestEnvironment

    public class RemoveLocatorsEmpty
extends Discovered
    With respect to the removeLocators method, this class verifies that the LookupLocatorDiscovery utility operates in a manner consistent with the specification. In particular, this class verifies that upon invoking the removeLocators method with the empty set, the set of locators the lookup locator discovery utility is configured to discover will not change. The environment in which this class expects to operate is as follows:

    • one or more lookup services
    • one instance of the lookup locator discovery utility initially configured to discover the set of locators whose elements are the locators of the initial lookup services
    • one instance of DiscoveryListener registered with the lookup locator discovery utility

    If the lookup locator discovery utility functions as specified, then after invoking the removeLocators method with the empty set, the contents of the managed set of locators with which the lookup locator discovery utility is configured prior to the invocation of removeLocators is the same as the contents of that set after removeLocators is invoked; and the listener will receive no discarded events.
